http://www.isid.org

Date: Mon 26 Sep 2016
Source: OIE, WAHID (World Animal Health Information Database), weekly disease information 2016; 29(39) [edited]
http://www.oie.int/wahis_2/public/wahid.php/Reviewreport/Review?page_refer=MapFullEventReport&reportid=21050


Bluetongue [BTV], Croatia
-------------------------
Information received on [and dated] 26 Sep 2016 from Dr Tomislav Kis, assistant to minister, Veterinary and Food Safety Directorate, Ministry of Agriculture, Zagreb, Croatia

Summary
Report type: immediate notification
Date of start of the event: 21 Sep 2016
Date of confirmation of the event: 26 Sep 2016
Reason for notification: reoccurrence of a listed disease
Date of previous occurrence: 1 Mar 2016
Manifestation of disease: clinical disease
Causal agent: bluetongue virus
Serotype: 4
Nature of diagnosis: clinical, laboratory (basic and advanced)
This event pertains to the whole country.

New outbreaks (2)
Outbreak 1: Glusci, Glusci, Metkovic, Dubrovačko-Neretvanska [Dubrovnik-Neretva]
Date of start of the outbreak: 21 Sep 2016
Outbreak status: continuing (or date resolved not provided)
Epidemiological unit: farm
Affected animals:
Species / Susceptible / Cases / Deaths / Destroyed / Slaughtered
Cattle / 3 / 0 / 0 / - / - /
Goats / 157 / 0 / 0 / - / - /
Sheep / 113 / 1 / 0 / - / - /

Outbreak 2: Glusci, Glusci, Metkovic, Dubrovačko-Neretvanska
Date of start of the outbreak: 21 Sep 2016
Outbreak status: continuing (or date resolved not provided)
Epidemiological unit: farm
Affected animals:
Species / Susceptible / Cases / Deaths / Destroyed / Slaughtered
Cattle/ 3 / 0 / 0 / - / - /
Sheep/ 30 / 2 / 0 / - / - /

Summary of outbreaks:
Total outbreaks: 2
Total animals affected:
Species / Susceptible / Cases / Deaths / Destroyed / Slaughtered
Cattle / 6 / 0 / 0 / - / - /
Goats / 157 / 0 / 0 / - / - /
Sheep / 143 / 3 / 0 / - / - /

Outbreak statistics [rates apparent, expressed in percentages]:
Species / Morbidity rate / Mortality rate / Case fatality rate / Proportion susceptible animals lost*
Cattle / 0 / 0 / ** / ** /
Goats / 0 / 0 / - / ** /
Sheep / 2.10 / 0 / 0 / ** /
* Removed from the susceptible population through death, destruction, and/or slaughter

Epidemiology
Source of the outbreak(s) or origin of infection: unknown or inconclusive
Epidemiological comments: non-vaccinated animals showed clinical signs. Bluetongue was confirmed by seroneutralization test and real-time PCR.

Control measures
Measures applied: vaccination permitted (if a vaccine exists); no treatment of affected animals
Measures to be applied: vaccination in response to the outbreak(s); disinfection/ disinfestations; control of vectors

Diagnostic test results
Laboratory name and type:
Croatian Veterinary Institute, Split (national laboratory)
Species / Test / Test date / Result
Sheep / real-time PCR / 26 Sep 2016 / Positive
Sheep/ seroneutralization test (SNT) / 26 Sep 2016 / Positive

Future reporting
The event is continuing. Weekly follow-up reports will be submitted.

[The location of these outbreaks can be seen on the interactive map included in the OIE report at the source URL above.]

--
Communicated by:
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>

[In January 2016, Croatia reported an outbreak of bluetongue serotype 4. The event was reported as resolved on 1 Mar 2016. According with the epidemiological comments in the final report: "All measures prescribed by legislation were carried out. In 2016 all population of bovine, ovine, and caprine is included in the vaccination programme. This latter will be terminated by 31 Mar 2016." See final report and map at http://www.oie.int/wahis_2/temp/reports/en_fup_0000019816_20160301_174625.pdf. - Mod.CRD

A HealthMap/ProMED-mail map can be accessed at: https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=4517491,55775.]
